{"TopicId":151901,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Can Fairings Be Auto Deployed?","CreatedByName":"Up The Ying Yang","CreatedById":125944,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T00:48:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Up The Ying Yang","CreatedById":125944,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T00:48:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was wondering.\u00A0Is there a way to have the fairings on a rocket\u00A0be auto-deployed at a specific altitude or air pressure?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T00:59:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think there\u0027s a straightforward mod to do this, but should be pretty easy in kOS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/61827-113-kos-scriptable-autopilot-system-v101-20161011/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Up The Ying Yang","CreatedById":125944,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T02:17:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222847538\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478912375\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sharpy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Sharpy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think there\u0027s a straightforward mod to do this, but should be pretty easy in kOS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/61827-113-kos-scriptable-autopilot-system-v101-20161011/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. I downloaded and installed. Following\u00A0the tutorial I found and added the control part and sent it out to the pad.\u00A0I then right clicked the part as the tutorial said but the popup didn\u0027t give me an option to open the screen. I don\u0027t know if this is a problem with me using 1.2.0 or a mod miss match.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: OK Fixed it. I needed to download the new pre-release update. Works fine now!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-12T03:01:16Z\u0022 title=\u002211/12/2016 03:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 12, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Up The Ying Yang\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ENew Info.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mbartelsm","CreatedById":78723,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T03:04:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGravity turn continued has an option for auto deploying\u00A0fairings depending on air pressure\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HvP","CreatedById":146104,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T04:08:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125944-up-the-ying-yang/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125944\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125944-up-the-ying-yang/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Up The Ying Yang\u003C/a\u003E You might find the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/58338-104-smart-parts-v166-dds-textures-and-bug-fixes-july-5/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ESmart Parts\u003C/a\u003E mod to be a simple and straightforward way of doing this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has little controller parts that you attach to your ship that will automatically activate stages, action groups, or even have nearby ships match your heading when the preset conditions are met. For your fairings you can set the conditions to stage an action group when the air pressure or altitude reaches a certain limit ascending, descending or both. Plus a lot more nifty uses.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-12T04:11:08Z\u0022 title=\u002211/12/2016 04:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 12, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by HvP\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Up The Ying Yang","CreatedById":125944,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T04:29:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222847603\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478919868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278723\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mbartelsm\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mbartelsm said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGravity turn continued has an option for auto deploying\u00A0fairings depending on air pressure\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes thanks. This is more what I\u0027m looking for. KOS is good but WAY over my head and complicated. I am not any good at coding at all.\u00A0\u003Cimg 